# Anti-AI-Slop Cheatsheet

> The single most important design reference. **Run on every DESIGN-mode response.** Refuse what you see, loudly. Cite this note.
>
> Source: Paul Bakaus's "Impeccable" slop catalog (37 documented AI tells) · the indigo-default story (Wathan, Aug 2025 — "every AI-generated interface on earth is purple") · prg.sh "Why Your AI Keeps Building the Same Purple Gradient Website."

## Color & Gradient — REFUSE

- [ ] Purple-to-blue / indigo-to-violet gradients. **The single most recognizable AI tell.**
- [ ] Default Tailwind / Material 3 indigo / violet / purple for primary actions.
- [ ] Pure `#000` background. Tint slightly toward brand hue.
- [ ] Gradient text on headlines / metrics.
- [ ] Dark-mode-with-neon-glow "cyberpunk by default."

## Typography — REFUSE

- [ ] Inter / Roboto / Geist / Plus Jakarta Sans / Space Grotesk / Fraunces as headline.
- [ ] One font family for everything.
- [ ] Monospace as shorthand for "we're technical."
- [ ] Body text in all-caps.
- [ ] Letter-spacing > 0.05em on body.
- [ ] Line-height < 1.3 on body.

## Layout — REFUSE

- [ ] **Side-tab thick-accent-border cards.** Per Impeccable: *"Thick colored border on one side of a card. The most recognizable tell of AI-generated UIs."*
- [ ] Icon-tile-above-heading feature-card template.
- [ ] Cards inside cards inside cards.
- [ ] Everything centered. Left-align by default.
- [ ] Identical card grids (icon + heading + 1-line copy, repeated 3 or 6 times).
- [ ] Hero-with-big-metric + three small supporting stats.
- [ ] Monotonous spacing (same gap value everywhere).
- [ ] Wrapping every piece of content in a bordered card.

## Components — REFUSE

- [ ] "Rounded-xl everywhere" reflex.
- [ ] Glassmorphism / blur / glow as decoration (only as layering tool).
- [ ] Every button styled as primary.
- [ ] Modals as default for non-trivial actions.
- [ ] **Flutter:** default Material 3 — default `ColorScheme.fromSeed`, default `CardTheme`, default centered `FAB`, default elevated-button radius. Override deliberately via `ThemeExtension`.
- [ ] Sparkline charts as decoration with no real data.

## Motion — REFUSE

- [ ] Bounce / elastic easing.
- [ ] Animating `width` / `height` / `padding` / `margin`.
- [ ] Wiggling icons, floating badges, "motion without meaning."

## Copy — REFUSE

- [ ] "Welcome to your dashboard." / "Get started in seconds." / "Built for teams."
- [ ] Redundant heading + sublabel + helper text saying the same thing.
- [ ] Apologetic empty states ("Oops, nothing here!").

## Imagery — REFUSE

- [ ] Generic stock illustrations.
- [ ] AI-generated illustrations on primary brand surfaces.

## Do THIS instead (positive playbook)

- One distinctive brand hue + 1–2 surprising accents, tuned in `oklch()`.
- Two distinct type families (display + body), ≥1.25 ratio between hierarchy steps.
- Left-align default. Intentional asymmetry (offset headlines, cards stick out 8px from grid, vary card sizes).
- Mixed radii on a committed rhythm.
- One primary button per surface, secondary ghost, tertiary text link.
- Real photography of the subject. Custom iconography or curated set (Phosphor, Lucide — TUNE stroke width).
- One orchestrated load reveal (stagger 3–5 elements, 60ms offsets, `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`).
- Haptics on primary action only.
- Empty states tell the user the next action, in voice.


